
--------------------------------
Type1 version of Nanum font 3.0
--------------------------------

Nanum font is a unicode font designed especially for the
Korean-language script, designed by Sandoll Communication
and Fontrix. It includes the sans serif (gothic), serif (myeongjo),
pen script and brush script typefaces. The publisher and distributor
is NHN Corp. (http://www.naver.com/)

The license of Nanum font is Open Font License 1.1
(http://help.naver.com/ops/step2/faq.nhn?faqId=15879)

Nanum font is available from Naver at http://hangeul.naver.com/font.

This package provides Type1 subfonts converted from Nanum Myeongjo
(Regular and ExtraBold) and Nanum Gothic (Regular and Bold) OTFs.
C70, LUC, T1, and TS1 font definition files are also provided.
This package does not include original OpenType/TrueType files.

FontForge/Perl scripts used for the conversion are available at
http://cvs.ktug.or.kr/viewcvs/ko.TeX/cjk-ko/fontutils/.

If you have comments about the package, please contact
Dohyun Kim <nomos at ktug or kr>. 

